  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 4 (Spell Level 2)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 3</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 17 | <b>Successes:</b> 2</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 5 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 17</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> E, Mob</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>This technique can only be performed if the target creature is your size category or smaller, and you are in a grapple with them. Make a grapple check. If successful, you deal your normal unarmed attack damage plus 3d6, and the target is left prone and no longer grappled by you. In addition, the target loses their Dexterity bonus to Defense until its next turn (Fortitude negates).</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Empower:</b> Spend 1 Chakra to increase the bonus damage by 1d6, up to 5d6 total bonus damage.</p>\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
